      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI below 5% for hemolysis index QoI; at least three mesh levels evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Three systematically refined meshes (4.2M, 11.7M, and 28.4M cells) were generated using consistent refinement ratios. GCI computed per Roache methodology yields a maximum of 2.1% for the hemolysis index across all five operating points. The fine-mesh solution is used for all subsequent analyses. Discretization error is well-controlled and the achieved level comfortably exceeds the MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental conditions documented with sufficient fidelity to permit meaningful comparison; fluid properties, rotational speed, and flow rate recorded.",
      "rationale": "Bench-top experiments were conducted using ovine blood at physiological hematocrit (40±2%). Pump speed and flow rate were set to match the five CFD operating points within ±1% tolerance. Temperature was controlled to 37°C. All test conditions are documented in the laboratory notebook and traceable to the CFD boundary conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH index within 15% of experimental measurement across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted relative hemolysis index agrees with experimental measurements within 12% across all five flow-speed combinations. The model systematically slightly under-predicts hemolysis at the highest shear condition (5 LPM, 3500 RPM), which is conservative for the intended worst-case identification purpose. The acceptance criterion of 15% is satisfied at all points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (hemolysis index) directly maps to the clinical endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index computed from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories. This QoI directly corresponds to the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1 used for predicate device comparison. The mapping from computational output to decision criterion is unambiguous and well-established in the literature."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
